title: dicopal
text:
1 dicopal
This is dicopal, an homage to the dicopal.js project. This website allows you to quickly browse a variety of color palettes and just copy their hex codes.

title: dicopal
text:
1.1 dicopal.js
dicopal.js deserves all credit for this work. I have only taken the palettes that they have collected and put them up on this page together with the hex codes. dicopal.js is using the Apache-2.0 license.
In total, dicopal.js has compiled color palettes with the following indentifiers:
[
  "cartocolors",
  "cmocean",
  "colorbrewer",
  "lightbartlein",
  "matplotlib",
  "mycarta",
  "scientific",
  "tableau",
  "wesanderson",
  "otakeito",
]

title: dicopal
text:
1.2 How to use?
Either go to dicopal.js to use these palettes or copy the provided hex codes and hard-code them in your application.
I just wanted to have a collection of useful and beautiful colormaps from which I can copy the corresponding hex values when needed.
